repoclient:

This package is designed to be installed on the VM to interface with the repoman server. 

To begin, run setup.py.  This will place a repoclient.conf in /etc/repoclient/.  Either edit this file or copy it to ~/.repoclient and insert your usercert, userkey and repository location.


Currently implemented commands:
repoman list [--all]
repoman getuser [--all]
repoman info --name imagename 
repoman save --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)]
repoman get --name imagename
repoman update [--force] --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)]
repoman share (--user username | --group groupname) [--read]  --image vmname
repoman unshare (--user username | --group groupname) [--read]  --image  vmname


Other metadata tag examples: --hypervisor Xen, --os_variant RHEL
All defaults are set in repoclient.conf, set in /etc/repoclient/repoclient.conf by default
